%N A397454 Decimal expansion of Product_{k>=5} cos(2*Pi/k).
%C A397454 A regular pentagram is inscribed in a unit circle, and a smaller circle is then inscribed within that pentagram. This process continues iteratively: a regular hexagram is inscribed in the second circle, followed by an inscribed circle within the hexagram, and so on. The radii of these circles converge to this constant.
%C A397454 The inscribed regular polygrams have the Schläfli symbol {k, 2} for k >= 5. They are regular star polygons when k is odd, and regular star figures (compound polygons) when k is even.
%H A397454 Amiram Eldar, <a href="/A397454/a397454.gif">Illustration</a>.
%H A397454 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/PolygonInscribing.html">Polygon Inscribing</a>.
%H A397454 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Polygram.html">Polygram</a>.
%H A397454 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/StarFigure.html">Star Figure</a>.
%H A397454 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/StarPolygon.html">Star Polygon</a>.
%H A397454 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kepler%E2%80%93Bouwkamp_constant">Kepler-Bouwkamp constant</a>.
%H A397454 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polygram_(geometry)">Polygram (geometry)</a>.
%H A397454 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Star_polygon">Star polygon</a>.
%F A397454 Equals exp(-Sum_{k>=1} ((2^(2*k)-1)/k) 2^(2*k) * zeta(2*k) * (zeta(2*k) - 1 - 1/2^(2*k) - 1/3^(2*k) - 1/4^(2*k))).
%F A397454 Equals 1/A397455.
%e A397454 0.00620134680380340104973610759107271741742698150617948...
%t A397454 With[{m = 1000}, RealDigits[Exp[NSum[-((2^(2*k) - 1)/k) 2^(2*k)*Zeta[2*k]*(Zeta[2*k] - 1 - 1/2^(2*k) - 1/3^(2*k) - 1/4^(2*k)), {k, 1, Infinity}, WorkingPrecision -> m, PrecisionGoal -> m, AccuracyGoal -> m, NSumTerms -> m]], 10, 120, -1][[1]]]
%o A397454 (PARI) exp(sumpos(k = 5, log(cos(2*Pi/k))))
